Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.55,Caption,,0,0,0,,On the fourth of June, 1996, a rocket\Nleft the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:04.55,0:00:06.37,Caption,,0,0,0,,ground in French Guiana.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:06.71,0:00:10.91,Caption,,0,0,0,,Thirty-seven seconds later, it tore\Nitself apart in the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:10.91,0:00:11.38,Caption,,0,0,0,,sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.72,0:00:16.30,Caption,,0,0,0,,No one was hurt. There was no sabotage.\NNo storm.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:16.30,0:00:20.87,Caption,,0,0,0,,No faulty wire, no cracked weld, no\Nengine that failed.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:21.21,0:00:24.65,Caption,,0,0,0,,The rocket worked perfectly. Every bolt,\Nevery valve,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.65,0:00:28.95,Caption,,0,0,0,,every gram of fuel did exactly what it\Nwas built
Dialogue: 10,0:00:28.95,0:00:29.81,Caption,,0,0,0,,to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:30.15,0:00:33.74,Caption,,0,0,0,,It was destroyed by a number. A single\Nnumber, in
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.74,0:00:37.33,Caption,,0,0,0,,a piece of software that wasn't even\Nsupposed to be
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.33,0:00:40.92,Caption,,0,0,0,,running — code that had already done its\Njob, copied
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.92,0:00:44.51,Caption,,0,0,0,,over from an older rocket because it had\Nnever once
Dialogue: 10,0:00:44.51,0:00:44.87,Caption,,0,0,0,,failed.
